# ============================================
# Request ID Format Explanation
# ============================================
# Cashwyre requires a unique requestId for each API call
# Format: req-{timestamp}-{random}
# Example: req-20250115T103045-ABC123
# 
# The generateRequestId() function creates:
# - Timestamp: ISO format without dashes/colons (20250115T103045)
# - Random: 6-character alphanumeric string (ABC123)
# - Combined: req-20250115T103045-ABC123
#
# This ensures:
# - Uniqueness (timestamp + random)
# - Traceability (timestamp for debugging)
# - Cashwyre compliance (unique per request)
